 a Scala trait versus a Java interface. A Scala trait acts like an interface with default methods, and I’m trying to make sense of abstract definitions. I’m writing a structure for a private class that extends an interface while considering method accessibility. I see that Java’s `getMethod` might return the declaring class if a method isn’t overridden in a subclass. I’m questioning if I need to override the method in my private class to make it work correctly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Ensuring class visibility**\\n\\nI'm considering class visibility in Scala. It seems the top-level public class must be public, and a Scala class without 'final' is public by default, which is good to know. I need to ensure that all top-level test classes are public, but for the MethodUtilsTest, that's covered. As for helpers, they can be either private or public, depending on their use. Alright, let's get to writing!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_YEvMmvR4sfNHdI5l2sKvDXrk|fc_077223540226434e016a29ab36ce9081979815626cab92fc57", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.typesafe.play/play_3/2.9.7/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_play/play_3/MethodUtilsTest.scala", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_typesafe_play.play_3\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method\nimport java.lang.reflect.Modifier\n\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\nimport play.libs.reflect.MethodUtils\n\nclass MethodUtilsTest {\n  @Test\n  def findsDirectPublicMethodByExactSignature(): Unit = {\n    val method: Method = MethodUtils.getMatchingAccessibleMethod(\n      classOf[DirectMethodTarget],\n      \"exact\",\n      classOf[String]\n    )\n\n    assertThat(method).isNotNull\n    assertThat(method.invoke(new DirectMethodTarget, \"play\")).isEqualTo(\"exact:play\")\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def scansPublicMethodsForAssignableSignature(): Unit = {\n    val method: Method = MethodUtils.getMatchingAccessibleMethod(\n      classOf[AssignableMethodTarget],\n      \"accept\",\n      classOf[String]\n    )\n\n    assertThat(method).isNotNull\n    assertThat(method.invoke(new AssignableMethodTarget, \"framework\")).isEqualTo(\"accepted:framework\")\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def resolvesAccessibleMethodFromPublicInterfaceImplementedByNonPublicClass(): Unit = {\n    val implementation: InterfaceBackedTarget = new PrivateInterfaceBackedTarget\n    val method: Method = classOf[PrivateInterfaceBackedTarget].getMethod(\"describe\", classOf[String])\n\n    val accessibleMethod: Method = MethodUtils.getAccessibleMethod(method)\n\n    assertThat(accessibleMethod).isNotNull\n    assertThat(accessibleMethod.getDeclaringClass).isEqualTo(classOf[InterfaceBackedTarget])\n    assertThat(accessibleMethod.invoke(implementation, \"routing\")).isEqualTo(\"interface:routing\")\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def resolvesAccessibleMethodFromPublicSuperclassOfNonPublicClass(): Unit = {\n    val implementation: PublicSuperclassTarget = new PrivateSuperclassBackedTarget\n    val method: Method = classOf[PrivateSuperclassBackedTarget].getMethod(\"fromSuperclass\", classOf[String])\n\n    val accessibleMethod: Method = MethodUtils.getAccessibleMethod(method)\n\n    assertThat(accessibleMethod).isNotNull\n    assertThat(Modifier.isPublic(accessibleMethod.getDeclaringClass.getModifiers)).isTrue\n    assertThat(accessibleMethod.getDeclaringClass).isEqualTo(classOf[PublicSuperclassTarget])\n    assertThat(accessibleMethod.invoke(implementation, \"configuration\")).isEqualTo(\"super:configuration\")\n  }\n}\n\nclass DirectMethodTarget {\n  def exact(value: String): String = s\"exact:$value\"\n}\n\nclass AssignableMethodTarget {\n  def accept(value: CharSequence): String = s\"accepted:$value\"\n}\n\ntrait InterfaceBackedTarget {\n  def describe(value: String): String\n}\n\nprivate final class PrivateInterfaceBackedTarget extends InterfaceBackedTarget {\n  override def describe(value: String): String = s\"interface:$value\"\n}\n\nclass PublicSuperclassTarget {\n  def fromSuperclass(value: String): String = s\"super:$value\"\n}\n\nprivate final class PrivateSuperclassBackedTarget extends PublicSuperclassTarget {\n  override def fromSuperclass(value: String): String = s\"private:$value\"\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3647, "output": 2362, "cacheRead": 15872, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21881, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781115661261, "responseId": "resp_077223540226434e016a29ab0db1bc8197b0b0d43815458f33"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_YEvMmvR4sfNHdI5l2sKvDXrk|fc_077223540226434e016a29ab36ce9081979815626cab92fc57", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 3093 bytes to tests/src/com.typesafe.play/play_3/2.9.7/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_play/play_3/MethodUtilsTest.scala"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1781115710199}]}
